[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'rhetoric101', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2021-07-29 18:54:28+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': '### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe

The scroll bar in the right gutter for "On this page" hides the vital content from our readers.  The power of having all the page headings available is that it enables readers to quickly skip to the section that interests them. When the headings are in a scroll box, it slows down readers, and readers may not notice the scroll bar.

### Describe the solution you'd like

How about removing the scroll bar for "On this page" so all headings appear--no matter what's in the right navigation pane?

### Describe why this important to you

I just got tripped up by this, thinking there we're only two headings on this complicated page: https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/infrastructure/install-infrastructure-agent/linux-installation/install-infrastructure-monitoring-agent-linux/

Let's try to reduce the friction for our readers by keeping the headings visible in the right gutter.', 'title': 'Remove scroll bar for  “On this page” in the right gutter', 'type': 'issue'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'TrainnosaurusRex', 'comment_id': 901408430.0, 'datetime': '2021-08-18 20:27:39+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': '+1 for this, the "related resources" are not as essential as the actual page contents.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'barbnewrelic', 'comment_id': 901416475.0, 'datetime': '2021-08-18 20:41:34+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': '+1 for this! For me, the "Related resources" is not particularly valuable, and it blocks the "On this page" content, which IS important. Two examples:
1-I was looking at a doc that I knew it had 8 specific agent-related H2s, but I could only see the first 2 headings, and I didn't immediately notice the vertical scrollbar because I'm using a tiny laptop. It looked like the doc had no agent-specific info to jump to, even though I knew it was there. If I was a casual docs site user, I might not even know there's more good content on the page unless I did CTRL F or scrolled down the page.
2-This morning I was docs hero, and an engineer asked in the documentation channel why a doc in the "Related resources" section was listed, even though we both knew that doc was completely unrelated to the doc he was currently viewing. The "Related resources" box added to the confusion and masked the content the engineer might have been more interested in on that page.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'barbnewrelic', 'comment_id': 923058246.0, 'datetime': '2021-09-20 15:57:21+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': "I got a message this issue will be automatically closed but I'm not clear if that's because a-GH bot thinks this is unimportant or b-if it has already been fixed. If a-please don't close, this is important! If b-thanks for fixing this!", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'barbnewrelic', 'comment_id': 1036432229.0, 'datetime': '2022-02-11 17:15:32+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': 'This is still a valid issue!', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'austin-schaefer', 'comment_id': 1037745397.0, 'datetime': '2022-02-13 04:05:39+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_3', 'text': 'Hi @username_0 @username_2 , can you link a doc where this is occuring? For me, I haven't seen this issue since we removed the "related resources" section.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'barbnewrelic', 'comment_id': 1038381828.0, 'datetime': '2022-02-13 19:45:23+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': 'The stalebot message threw me, because I was unaware that this had been fixed. I thought the workflow was, if a someone fixes an issue, they make a note in their PR like "Fixes 3335." I did not see any "fixed" message. Just did a spot check of a couple of docs that have a lot of headings, and they all appear nicely in the right nav now. Please extend my thanks to whoever fixed this issue!', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}]

